main event: On 3 June 1953, Mrs. C. H. Warren observed an unidentified aerial object in the Muster, Texas area.
interesting points: Mrs. Warren observed a very bright light in the southern sky, approximately 300 feet in altitude., The object appeared to be diving and climbing at a rapid rate of speed., The observation lasted for approximately 15 minutes., The sighting occurred on a clear night with stars visible., Mrs. Warren was quite disturbed about the incident and believed it was some type of unidentified aerial object.
sighted object: a very bright light in the southern sky
witness description: Mrs. C. H. Warren, a civilian
